uniol.apt.compiler

Class AbstractServiceProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.annotation.processing.AbstractProcessor
      • uniol.apt.compiler.AbstractServiceProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javax.annotation.processing.Processor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractAptServiceProcessor, AbstractSPIServiceProcessor

    public abstract class AbstractServiceProcessor
extends javax.annotation.processing.AbstractProcessor
    Abstract annotation processor base class which scans for an annotation, analyzes all classes marked by this annotation and writes their names in files in META-INF
    Author:
    vsp

    • Method Detail

      • visitClass

        protected abstract void visitClass(javax.lang.model.element.TypeElement classEle,
                                   java.lang.String className)
        Function that is called on every annotated class that is visited. During process, every class that is annotated with our annotation has some sanity-checks applied (e.g. does it implement the required interface) and then this function is called on it.
        Parameters:
        classEle - The TypeElement that represents the class that is being compiled.
        className - The name of the class represented by classEle.

      • writeResourceList

        protected void writeResourceList(java.lang.String resourceName,
                                 java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> entries)
                          throws java.io.IOException
        Function that writes a resource list into the class output directory. Existing entries are preserved. This means that this function only ever adds new entries.
        Parameters:
        resourceName - Name of the file in which the resource list should be saved.
        entries - Entries that should be added to the list.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - In case I/O errors occur.
